<docbook><section><title>MySQLPrepareMethod</title><para> </para><bridgehead class="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml:h2"> What does the MySQL Prepare Method Do? </bridgehead>
<para>The MySQL prepare method enables you to specify how MySQL will prepare SQL queries.
 The options are:</para><itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="compact"><listitem> 0 - Don&#39;t use MySQL Prepare/Execute features</listitem>
</itemizedlist><itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="compact"><listitem> 1 - Use Prepare/Execute features only for queries with parameters</listitem>
</itemizedlist><itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="compact"><listitem> 2 - Use Prepare/Execute features for all queries with parameters &amp; all select queries(with and without parameters) </listitem>
</itemizedlist></section></docbook>